summary: This document contains three Florida traffic citation reports from the Palm Beach Police Department for Ghislaine Maxwell. The citations include a driver license violation and two written warnings for traffic infractions in Palm Beach, Florida, in 1996.

keyFacts: Ghislaine Maxwell received multiple traffic citations in Palm Beach, Florida, in 1996.
One citation was for not carrying a driver's license (TC037) on January 13, 1996.
She received a written warning for passing double yellow lines on the same date.
She received another written warning for an illegal left turn on August 10, 1996.
The documents show Maxwell was driving a 1986 Mercedes with Florida license plates while holding a UK driver's license.
